<topic template="Default" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">RES: Reservoir Package Pane</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">RES: Reservoir Package Pane</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The Reservoir package simulates leakage between a reservoir and an underlying groundwater system as the reservoir area expands and contracts in response to changes in reservoir stage. Unlike the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="LAK_Lake_Package_Pane" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Lake</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> package the user specifies the heads in reservoirs rather than the heads being computed. &#160;The pane for this package is on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Packages_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Packages and Programs</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box under </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Head_Dependant_Flux" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Head Dependant Flux</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">On the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">RES: Reservoir package pane</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, the user can specify where the reservoirs will be located. &#160;Possible choices include (1) the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Top layer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, (2) a </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Specified layer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and (3) </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Top active cell</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. &#160;However, if </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Top active cell</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is picked, the location of the reservoir will NOT change vertically in response to cells switching between wet and dry.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">The user also chooses whether to </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Print reservoir stage, area, and volume at each time step (IRESPT)</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">number of values in the printed table of stage, volume, and area (NPTS).</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> &#160;First and last stage value are minimum and maximum elevations within area of potential inundation. A value of 15 or greater is recommended for detailed representation of stage-volume and stage-area relations.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
